events.body:
Concept ACK.

What is changed since #17240?
Idk, they seem to pass, so why not enable them again and give it a shot?

Passed once: https://travis-ci.org/github/bitcoin/bitcoin/jobs/679893016#L3111

Open-Close to re-run ci. See https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/15847#issuecomment-487591130

Concept ACK, I didn't even remember we turned them off.

I find that logging out of Travis and back in restores my ability to restart jobs.
`wallet_multiwallet.py` failed, presumably randomly. I restarted it.
Please don't restart without saving the log. Otherwise, the issue can not be fixed.
ACK fac24dea00c54fe1e2dcc7625bb65ada8b97ac0c, verified travis build log.

issue.title: test: macOS functional tests still failing intermittently
issue.body: The functional tests were re-enabled on macOS in #18778. However it looks like they are still suffering from intermittent failures. i.e: https://travis-ci.org/github/bitcoin/bitcoin/jobs/680353191#L3136. The `OSError: [Errno 41] Protocol wrong type for socket` error in feature_assumevalid looks like the same one that was reported in #17240 when the tests were first disabled.
